18:58.040 --> 19:00.031
Are you sure you're not
under the influence?

19:00.120 --> 19:02.270
I was asleep by... 11.30.

19:02.360 --> 19:05.557
I said I'd take nothing
and I took nothing.

19:05.640 --> 19:08.871
I had nowt but water at Eva Braun's
welcome home. Hand on heart.

19:10.600 --> 19:12.431
Test me piss, if you like.

19:12.520 --> 19:14.351
I want me kids back!

19:15.920 --> 19:17.592
Nice one, Dad.

19:23.800 --> 19:25.279
HE YAWNS

19:25.360 --> 19:28.716
I'd forgotten what it feels like
to have blood flowing through me veins

19:28.800 --> 19:31.792
- instead of 5% imported lager.
- Why don't you get yourself ready?

19:31.880 --> 19:34.440
Shirt's ironed, on the back
of your bedroom door.

19:48.680 --> 19:51.433
HE EXHALES

19:51.520 --> 19:53.033
God, I feel alive!

19:53.120 --> 19:55.031
- Where have you been?
- Out.

19:55.120 --> 19:58.032
You've been hours. I was worried.
Your mobile went straight to voicemail.

19:58.120 --> 20:02.796
Stan, will you back off?
You're suffocating me!

20:02.880 --> 20:05.917
You can be a little overbearing
at times.

20:06.000 --> 20:07.558
Fuck... off!

20:15.320 --> 20:16.673
What's going on?

20:26.600 --> 20:30.354
I've come to apologise.
I'm doing this for Mandy.

20:30.440 --> 20:32.954
I love her,
and we want to make a go of it.

20:33.040 --> 20:34.792
She needs her family.

20:34.880 --> 20:37.110
She's got her family.

20:38.360 --> 20:40.794
Karen?
See what this bloke wants, will you?

20:47.560 --> 20:51.314
I thought you might have a smile for me,
after everything we've been through.

20:51.400 --> 20:52.469
Don't push your luck.

20:52.560 --> 20:55.028
- Imagine what Jamie'd do if he knew.
- Well, he'd kill you.

20:55.120 --> 20:58.351
Well, he'd have to be quick.
Cos if he thinks I'm going to let him

20:58.440 --> 21:01.955
have a pop at me twice, he's more thick
than I had him marked down for.

21:02.040 --> 21:04.952
Three lagers, pint of Guinness,

21:05.040 --> 21:07.349
orange and ice...

21:07.440 --> 21:10.432
a voddy tonic for Laughing Gas.

21:10.520 --> 21:13.273
I want you to build some bridges.

21:13.360 --> 21:16.591
Between me and your hubby.
Convince him that I mean what I say,

21:16.680 --> 21:19.990
that I'm head over heels for his sister
and that I'm a changed man.

21:20.080 --> 21:22.150
That he actually beat
some sense into me.

21:22.240 --> 21:24.117
You're wasting your time.

21:24.200 --> 21:25.553
Try.

21:25.640 --> 21:27.870
And remember,

21:27.960 --> 21:31.873
I can walk away from this
at any time I like. You can't.

21:31.960 --> 21:35.236
No, but you're presuming I want to.
Or that I need to.

21:35.320 --> 21:37.914
You tell Jamie what went on
between me and you.

21:38.000 --> 21:40.150
Just see who he believes.

21:40.240 --> 21:43.038
His wife, who he wants to have his kids,

21:43.120 --> 21:47.113
or the piece of shit
that near bust his sister's ribs.

21:47.200 --> 21:50.033
That's L8, please, Joe.

21:51.840 --> 21:53.319
Take one for yourself.

21:53.400 --> 21:54.674
No, thanks.

21:55.920 --> 21:59.390
As you know, I have to submit
a report to my superiors

21:59.480 --> 22:04.395
about the possibility of Stella
and Liam's return to the family home.

22:04.480 --> 22:07.870
Can we read it first? Make sure
you're not putting any lies down.

22:07.960 --> 22:10.428
- Debbie...
- Well, she's not trustworthy, is she?

22:10.520 --> 22:12.431
Made mates with us last time,

22:12.520 --> 22:14.590
pissed off with the kids
as soon as our back was turned.

22:14.680 --> 22:16.716
- That's enough.
- It's not like you're not thinking it.

22:16.800 --> 22:18.597
This isn't helping, Debbie.

22:21.720 --> 22:25.315
I did what I had to do.
We will not leave children in a home

22:25.400 --> 22:27.834
where there are drugs
or alcohol being abused.

22:27.920 --> 22:29.831
All that's over. It's different.

22:29.920 --> 22:33.151
I've changed, seen the light.

22:33.240 --> 22:35.993
You know you hear about
people saying that

22:36.080 --> 22:39.550
they'd die for their sons and daughters,
leap in front of bullets for them?

22:39.640 --> 22:42.950
I used to think, "Bollocks.
You can always have more kids."

22:43.960 --> 22:45.313
But...

22:45.400 --> 22:47.197
I understand now.

22:47.280 --> 22:50.238
I mean, losing Liam and Stella,

22:50.320 --> 22:56.156
it's made me reassess
what I want out of life.

22:56.240 --> 22:58.151
And what I want...

22:58.240 --> 23:00.151
first and foremost...

23:00.240 --> 23:03.038
is my kids back.

23:04.160 --> 23:07.914
- So what is it we need to do?
- Well, what we're looking for initially

23:08.000 --> 23:12.232
is an improvement
re certain safety issues.

23:12.320 --> 23:16.393
But I can see that there has been
a huge advance in that regard,

23:16.480 --> 23:19.199
but it's their emotional security
that's my main concern.

23:19.280 --> 23:23.558
I know Debbie does her best,
but you don't need me to tell you

23:23.640 --> 23:26.279
that it's not her place to look after
two young children.

23:26.360 --> 23:28.555
Well, I hold me hands up.

23:28.640 --> 23:33.430
I have made mistakes,
but... a lot of that is

23:33.520 --> 23:38.514
to do with the fall-out of my wife
leaving me to cope on my own and...

23:38.600 --> 23:40.955
Well, simply, I couldn't.

23:43.240 --> 23:50.510
Er... I wasn't ready for, you know,
the responsibility then. But I am now.

23:50.600 --> 23:56.197
And he will have back-up. I know
I'm not officially part of the family,

23:56.280 --> 23:59.989
but they took me to their hearts
when I had no-one,

24:00.080 --> 24:03.152
and I'd like to repay that kindness

24:03.240 --> 24:07.518
by doing whatever I can to make sure
Liam and Stella are safe and secure.

24:14.480 --> 24:16.391
I'm still awake, aren't I?

24:16.480 --> 24:19.916
And that's got to be a good thing,
knowing that we've got that...

24:20.000 --> 24:23.709
support from Norma,
that back-up, whenever...

24:27.080 --> 24:28.513
...we need it.

24:31.000 --> 24:33.195
Oh, shit!

24:34.240 --> 24:36.037
I know you think I'm stupid.

24:36.120 --> 24:40.238
I know he's not the man
you'd have picked for me, but...

24:40.320 --> 24:42.880
you can't help who you fall
in love with, can you, Mam?

24:45.640 --> 24:47.631
I just wish I could be stronger.

24:47.720 --> 24:48.914
More like you.

24:51.200 --> 24:53.998
We're more alike
than you'll ever know.

24:58.280 --> 25:01.431
- You knew what was riding on this!
- I'm sorry. I should have remembered.

25:01.520 --> 25:04.239
If I'd don't have a drink,
or a spliff or an E...

25:04.320 --> 25:06.675
If I don't anaesthetise myself,
the hormones kick in

25:06.760 --> 25:09.354
and Lickle Frank thinks he's 15.

25:09.440 --> 25:13.115
Oh, come on! Who the fuck's
going to be attracted to Norma?

25:13.200 --> 25:14.315
Your wife, for one!

25:14.400 --> 25:17.517
I am the victim of a liberated libido.

25:17.600 --> 25:19.830
Anything can get Lickle Frank going.
Sitting on the back of the bus,

25:19.920 --> 25:21.797
flicking through the knicker section
of the catalogue,

25:21.880 --> 25:23.598
and don't say you don't know
what I'm talking about.

25:23.680 --> 25:24.749
You fuck off!

25:24.840 --> 25:27.115
Come on. Out of all of them,
you're most like me -

25:27.200 --> 25:28.758
your brains are in your bollocks.

25:28.840 --> 25:31.035
Come on, help me out.
You know what it's like.

25:31.120 --> 25:32.951
I'm nothing like you, all right?

25:33.040 --> 25:35.838
If Debbie hadn't had a go
at that social worker,

25:35.920 --> 25:37.478
none of this would have happened.

25:37.560 --> 25:39.994
No, you fucked it up, not Debbie!

25:40.080 --> 25:42.833
You've fucked it up with
each and every one of us, Dad.

25:42.920 --> 25:45.388
You had the chance
to put it right with Liam and Stella

25:45.480 --> 25:46.959
but you fucked that up, too.

25:48.600 --> 25:51.558
- I'm sorry.
- Aren't you always?

25:51.640 --> 25:53.073
I am!

25:54.760 --> 25:57.354
Will that bring your kids back?

26:01.960 --> 26:05.316
Liam? It's Debbie.
Look, I'm on my way round.

26:05.400 --> 26:06.833
Make sure you're in.

26:32.200 --> 26:34.316
DOOR CLOSES

26:37.200 --> 26:38.633
Hello?

26:49.360 --> 26:52.238
Not a bad place. Got potential.

26:52.320 --> 26:55.835
- How d'you find me?
- I followed you from your dad's. Yours?

26:55.920 --> 26:58.957
Must be worth a few bob. Sugar daddy?

26:59.040 --> 27:02.350
Some rich eccentric pop his clogs
after slotting you one?

27:02.440 --> 27:04.954
Don't talk to me like that.
I'm not 15 any more.

27:05.040 --> 27:07.429
- What are you after?
- Why would I want anything?

27:07.520 --> 27:10.796
Because it's the only time I ever saw you
with a fucking smile on your face.

27:10.880 --> 27:16.034
I missed you. Realised how wrong
I got it when we were together,

27:16.120 --> 27:19.510
how stupid I was
throwing what we had away.

27:20.680 --> 27:22.318
How much I loved you...

27:22.400 --> 27:25.153
That wouldn't have worked on me
even when I was a kid.

27:25.240 --> 27:26.593
What are you really after?

27:26.680 --> 27:29.717
I need somewhere to crash.
I wouldn't ask if I wasn't desperate.

27:29.800 --> 27:31.870
Do I look like I give a fuck?

27:31.960 --> 27:34.997
How about a couple of quid,
you know, just tide me over?

27:36.120 --> 27:39.510
They said they'd kill me!
If I don't pay back what I owe.

27:39.600 --> 27:42.194
Kill me, lan! Ten grand!

27:42.280 --> 27:44.032
I ain't got that sort of cash.

27:44.120 --> 27:47.635
Well, sell this place. Take out
a fucking loan! I'm desperate here.

27:51.400 --> 27:54.153
Fuck you, then. Fuck... you!

28:06.160 --> 28:08.116
- Hiya.
- Hiya, Debbie. Come in.

28:08.880 --> 28:10.677
I would have called, but...

28:10.760 --> 28:14.594
It's OK. I said you could call
any time, and I meant it.

28:14.680 --> 28:17.069
Thanks.
BABY CRIES

28:17.160 --> 28:18.149
Can I pick her up?

28:20.160 --> 28:21.832
So how's things?

28:23.440 --> 28:26.910
I just miss them both like mad.
How's Liam been?

28:27.000 --> 28:28.911
Ask him yourself.

28:30.480 --> 28:32.994
Can we go out? Town maybe?

28:33.080 --> 28:35.833
- We could go for a pizza.
- I'd have to come with you.

28:35.920 --> 28:38.150
Rules, Debbie. Sorry.

28:40.280 --> 28:41.474
Sure.

28:42.600 --> 28:45.160
Hiya, hello.

28:45.240 --> 28:46.992
I know he was a bastard.

28:47.080 --> 28:50.993
I know he tret me like shit
and the kids even worse.

28:51.080 --> 28:54.231
I know I should have told him
to fuck off, Stan.

28:55.840 --> 28:59.628
When he were there, telling me
he'd realised what a mistake he'd made

28:59.720 --> 29:01.278
and how sorry he was,

29:01.360 --> 29:04.830
I just remembered
how much I used to love him.

29:06.440 --> 29:08.192
I just wanted to help.

29:11.600 --> 29:14.239
If you love him,
tell me, and I'll walk away.

29:14.320 --> 29:17.278
<i>No! No, Stan. I love you.</i>

29:18.880 --> 29:21.155
I just felt so sorry for him.

29:22.640 --> 29:25.677
And that, if that can help him find

29:25.760 --> 29:29.469
just a little bit of happiness
in his life, it'll be worth every penny.

29:39.000 --> 29:42.549
The whole family's in pieces.
Dad's taking it particularly bad.

29:42.640 --> 29:45.712
I'm sure it won't be long before
you're all together again.

29:45.800 --> 29:47.597
What does your social worker say?

29:47.680 --> 29:50.069
She's got to get the reports in,
see what the bosses recommend.

29:50.160 --> 29:51.639
Oh, darling.

30:00.440 --> 30:01.919
- Maria!
- I'll get it.

30:30.560 --> 30:32.073
Are you OK?

30:32.160 --> 30:33.559
Aaaaargh!

30:36.880 --> 30:38.916
Do you want to call it a day?

30:44.960 --> 30:47.110
I can't afford to grow a conscience, son.

30:47.200 --> 30:49.191
Where to next?

30:49.280 --> 30:51.396
Are you going straight back on duty, then?

30:51.480 --> 30:54.119
No rest for the wicked.

30:54.200 --> 30:56.873
Thanks again, Lillian.

30:56.960 --> 30:58.837
You still on for tonight?

30:58.920 --> 31:01.912
I wouldn't miss it for the world,
Mr Huckenhall.

31:02.000 --> 31:04.833
- Colin... please.
- Oh, right.

31:15.240 --> 31:17.674
L2,372.

31:17.760 --> 31:20.558
Thanks, Von.
You don't know what this means.

31:20.640 --> 31:23.154
She knows exactly what it means.

31:23.240 --> 31:26.391
It means you're L7,628 short.

31:26.480 --> 31:29.552
I've ordered the cash from the bank,
I'll bring it to you later.

31:29.640 --> 31:31.949
Why didn't you just tell the truth?

31:32.040 --> 31:34.759
All that shit about
loving me and the kids.

31:34.840 --> 31:37.832
- All that was true!
- Bollocks! You tried that with me.

31:37.920 --> 31:39.592
Using your own kids

31:39.680 --> 31:43.275
- to get a few bob out of her.
- Take it back, then. Go on, take it.

31:43.360 --> 31:45.157
If that's all you think I'm here for.

31:45.240 --> 31:47.754
(Stan) If that's all it takes to get
rid of you, it's worth every penny.

31:47.840 --> 31:52.470
You get it on the understanding that
you never set foot back here again.

31:52.560 --> 31:55.791
Try and contact the kids,
and I'll fucking kill you.

31:55.880 --> 31:58.314
And if she doesn't, I will.

31:58.400 --> 31:59.913
And if they don't...

32:00.000 --> 32:01.718
Yeah, I got the message.

32:03.920 --> 32:06.309
If there was any other way, Yvonne.

32:07.760 --> 32:09.432
I just got in over me head.

32:09.520 --> 32:11.875
Borrowed too much money
from the wrong kind of people.

32:11.960 --> 32:14.269
I'll drop the cash here tonight.
Seven o'clock.

32:16.280 --> 32:17.554
What?

32:19.160 --> 32:20.639
I had no option.

32:28.520 --> 32:31.717
<i>This will do the trick, won't it?
This will be the last we see of him.</i>

32:31.800 --> 32:34.758
I already thought that were the last
I'd seen of him.

32:34.840 --> 32:37.638
We've got to make him understand,
there's no more after this has gone.

32:37.720 --> 32:41.190
There's the shop. That's what
worries me, he knows I've got the shop.

32:41.280 --> 32:43.669
Where the fuck is this gonna end
short of killing the little shit?

32:43.760 --> 32:45.955
- Be serious.
- I am.

33:15.200 --> 33:16.713
And the cupboard was bare.

33:29.440 --> 33:31.431
I didn't know if you'd be in
after what you said.

33:31.520 --> 33:35.559
I thought you might be out, you know,
shagging women, trying drugs.

33:35.640 --> 33:39.918
Asserting your masculinity.
Not that I've got a problem with that.

33:44.000 --> 33:45.797
Could do you a fry-up in ten.

33:45.880 --> 33:47.598
Sit down.

33:47.680 --> 33:49.671
It's your house, after all.

33:54.840 --> 33:55.909
MIMI CLEARS THROAT

33:56.000 --> 33:59.834
I was just thinking...
about what you said earlier.

34:03.320 --> 34:06.312
And if those are the conditions
I have to agree to

34:06.400 --> 34:09.676
in order for this marriage
to survive... then so be it.

34:09.760 --> 34:11.318
Yeah?

34:12.520 --> 34:13.998
I've got one condition.

34:14.080 --> 34:15.274
Name it.

34:15.360 --> 34:18.112
You never bring
any of the women home.

34:18.199 --> 34:20.156
Done.

34:24.520 --> 34:27.353
And what's sauce for the goose
is sauce for the gander.

34:27.440 --> 34:32.195
I've been on the internet. There's
an escort agency in Deansgate.

34:32.280 --> 34:37.877
150 quid gets me an hour with Mike,
a student at the uni. Australian.

34:37.960 --> 34:41.793
44 inch chest, 32 inch waist,

34:41.880 --> 34:44.393
and a cock like a baby's arm
holding a peach.

34:47.199 --> 34:50.431
Speaking of which,
fruit salad OK for afters?

34:50.520 --> 34:52.795
Take the peaches out.

34:53.159 --> 34:56.118
I saw that look in your eye,
Stan, and it frightened me.

34:56.159 --> 34:58.628
Right, OK. I want to kill him!

34:58.720 --> 35:00.711
I could strangle the fucker
with me bare hands!

35:02.320 --> 35:05.676
- Got any Eccles cakes?
- We're right out. Sorry.

35:08.560 --> 35:11.074
That bastard has the audacity
to come back in here

35:11.160 --> 35:13.958
after all these years
and threaten everything we have.

35:14.040 --> 35:17.919
I could slit his throat, I could
peel the fucker, stab the twat!

35:18.000 --> 35:19.877
I could bury him alive.
Electrocute him!

35:19.960 --> 35:24.556
I could hammer nails
through his thick fucking skull!

35:24.640 --> 35:26.870
I could eat him.
Yeah, that's right, I could eat him.

35:26.960 --> 35:29.190
But I wouldn't cook the cunt.

35:29.280 --> 35:31.510
I'd eat the fucker raw!

35:35.800 --> 35:37.791
What is it doing to us?

35:37.880 --> 35:40.075
What's it turning us into?

35:40.160 --> 35:44.631
You're right. Oh, dear God,
I'm sorry, Yvonne. You're right.

35:44.720 --> 35:46.153
What was I thinking?

35:46.240 --> 35:49.915
We don't need this.
It's all just material stuff.

35:50.000 --> 35:51.194
It can be replaced.

35:52.440 --> 35:57.833
What's important is
me, you and the kids.

35:57.920 --> 36:02.596
We stay one step ahead of Kash,
and we tell the kids everything.

36:02.680 --> 36:04.318
We go to the police now.

36:04.400 --> 36:08.916
Tell them about the sham suicide
and the phoney insurance claim.

36:09.000 --> 36:13.471
We'll go down for it, but they'll be
lenient if we co-operate, which we will.

36:13.560 --> 36:16.597
We're looking at five, ten years, max.

36:16.680 --> 36:18.910
But... we'll keep our dignity,

36:19.000 --> 36:23.232
be able to hold our heads high in
the knowledge that there's no-one

36:23.320 --> 36:27.472
out there with anything over us.
We're better than him, Yvonne.

36:27.560 --> 36:30.757
- Ten years?
- Max.

36:30.840 --> 36:33.718
Fuck that. Let's kill him.

36:38.600 --> 36:41.717
You took her without permission?

36:41.800 --> 36:45.236
Which means effectively
you've kidnapped Stella. And Liam.

36:45.320 --> 36:47.834
- No.
- Why can't we go home?

36:47.920 --> 36:49.592
Cos Soft Shite has got
half of Manchester's finest

36:49.680 --> 36:51.955
combing the estate looking for you two.

36:52.040 --> 36:56.477
- You wanted them back - here they are.
- Quiet! We need to sort this and quick.

36:56.560 --> 37:00.519
- Has the carer tried ringing you?
- I haven't had my phone turned on.

37:00.600 --> 37:02.272
Say there's been a mix-up.

37:02.360 --> 37:05.955
What happened on the bus
was a genuine mistake.

37:06.040 --> 37:09.077
You didn't charge your phone,
you panicked and ran back here.

37:09.160 --> 37:10.275
I just hope they believe you.

37:15.200 --> 37:17.839
Hang on, Debs.
Let's just try one more thing.

37:19.040 --> 37:21.190
Colin wants us to do it al fresco.
Think I should?

37:21.280 --> 37:25.831
Why not? Start by half six,
most people are in having their tea.

37:25.920 --> 37:27.512
MOANING

37:31.200 --> 37:34.112
Don't we normally do stock-take
at night?

37:34.200 --> 37:36.316
Do you want the 30 quid, or don't you?

37:36.400 --> 37:38.675
Well get in there
and shut the fuck up.

37:42.800 --> 37:45.519
Three hours. Plenty of time.
We can afford to chill out a bit.

37:45.600 --> 37:47.636
- Get our heads clear.
- We can do this.

37:47.720 --> 37:49.392
We can do...

37:49.480 --> 37:53.871
Yvonne! You said ages back
you used to be a foster carer.

37:56.520 --> 37:57.839
We need a favour.

38:04.360 --> 38:05.839
So what is it you're suggesting?

38:05.920 --> 38:07.751
I'm still registered. The kids come to me

38:07.840 --> 38:10.638
while the family re-adjust
to the new circumstances.

38:10.720 --> 38:13.792
- Monica doing a bunk.
- It's not that easy, Yvonne.

38:13.880 --> 38:15.916
I know you've got reservations
about Frank's abilities as a parent.

38:16.000 --> 38:17.513
Who hasn't?

38:17.600 --> 38:19.431
Take a positive step.

38:19.520 --> 38:21.556
If I'm allowed to foster the kids,
they're just next door,

38:21.640 --> 38:24.837
close proximity to the siblings,
lower stress levels for everyone.

38:24.920 --> 38:27.593
- Yours included.
- But what about their father?

38:27.680 --> 38:31.150
He can barely look after himself.
Where is he, anyhow?

38:31.240 --> 38:34.357
He's popped down to see his best mate.

38:36.880 --> 38:38.632
Aaah!

38:38.720 --> 38:41.837
Let's not write him off just yet.
If I'm approved, it should be

38:41.920 --> 38:43.911
on the condition
he attends parenting classes.

38:47.560 --> 38:50.074
Look, you know as well as I do

38:50.160 --> 38:53.118
that once you put this to your bosses,
they'll bite your hand off.

38:53.200 --> 38:55.236
One less family on the at-risk register,

38:55.320 --> 38:57.629
I'm back on your books,
you're throwing kids at me

38:57.720 --> 39:02.350
left, right and centre and I'll take
them. I'll help you, you help me.

39:06.000 --> 39:08.036
Well... it couldn't be immediate.

39:08.120 --> 39:12.238
Oh, no! We couldn't cope with immediate.

39:12.320 --> 39:14.880
We've got a few things
to get out of the way first.

39:14.960 --> 39:18.077
Can we have tea here,
then go back to Maria's later?

39:20.200 --> 39:24.159
Then you put your report in, tell them
the brilliant idea you've come up with.

39:24.240 --> 39:25.389
Brownie points for you,

39:25.480 --> 39:28.199
kids are back where they belong,
everybody's happy.

39:29.600 --> 39:32.433
- Back in Maria's by nine?
- Deal.

39:33.960 --> 39:36.679
- Oh, Yvonne, man!
- No need. Bye!

39:41.200 --> 39:44.749
I won't be able to keep it to myself.

39:44.840 --> 39:46.990
- I'll tell people. I'll confess.
- Tell them what?

39:47.080 --> 39:48.433
That we killed him.

39:48.520 --> 39:51.353
He's dead already,
how do you kill a dead man? Look...

39:51.440 --> 39:55.228
we've still got an hour.
Let's go over it one more time.

39:55.320 --> 39:58.835
<i>(Stan) You prep the room,
make it forensic proof.</i>

39:58.920 --> 40:00.717
<i>I make myself scarce.</i>

40:01.680 --> 40:03.398
<i>We wait.</i>

40:05.080 --> 40:08.277
<i>(Yvonne) When he turns up,
I keep him talking.</i>

40:08.360 --> 40:11.158
<i>Some guff about
you fetching the money.</i>

40:12.680 --> 40:14.671
<i>I keep him busy, while you...</i>

40:15.480 --> 40:17.516
Then, once he's dead,

40:17.600 --> 40:19.955
I bought a season ticket
to Knowsley Safari Park.

40:20.040 --> 40:23.828
Go as many times as we like,
but I think it'll only take four trips.

40:23.920 --> 40:25.876
Arms, legs, torso, head.

40:25.960 --> 40:28.918
Once we've driven
into the lion enclosure,

40:29.000 --> 40:31.719
it's windows down
and bye-bye, Kash.

40:36.720 --> 40:37.755
OK.

40:38.800 --> 40:39.915
OK.

40:49.400 --> 40:52.198
RADIO PLAYS

40:56.640 --> 40:58.039
DOOR OPENS

41:14.840 --> 41:16.353
How the fuck did you get in? We're closed.

41:20.120 --> 41:21.553
Kept my keys.

41:33.680 --> 41:35.636
MUSIC PLAYS

41:50.920 --> 41:52.956
I'm sorry I lied.

41:53.040 --> 41:55.952
But believe me, son, I had no choice.

41:56.040 --> 41:58.634
If I hadn't, you, your mum, Meena...

41:58.720 --> 42:01.871
you'd have lost everything.
Everything.

42:03.040 --> 42:05.873
- They said you killed yourself.
- It was the only way

42:05.960 --> 42:09.316
I could think of getting you
out of the mess that I'd made.

42:09.400 --> 42:11.311
I went to your funeral.

42:12.720 --> 42:15.837
- I'm sorry.
- I prayed every night for your soul.

42:17.400 --> 42:19.994
- Fuck off!
- Please, son.

42:20.080 --> 42:23.072
I said fuck off. I mean fuck off!

42:31.560 --> 42:35.473
He's not coming.
There's summat wrong, I can feel it.

42:39.080 --> 42:41.719
- You lied.
- I had no choice.

42:41.800 --> 42:44.030
You could have told me,
you could have trusted me!

42:44.120 --> 42:45.951
If I'd stayed,
I would've taken you down with me.

42:46.040 --> 42:47.268
I'd have gone with you!

42:49.400 --> 42:51.277
I'd have gone.

43:02.440 --> 43:03.714
I'm sorry.

43:15.000 --> 43:16.479
<i>I wish you were dead.</i>

43:16.560 --> 43:18.312
You bastard!

43:18.400 --> 43:21.039
FIREWORKS EXPLODE

43:25.640 --> 43:27.278
Shit!

43:32.560 --> 43:36.792
♪ Let's face the music and dance... ♪

43:52.560 --> 43:54.278
Hiya, kid.

43:55.200 --> 43:56.918
I'm sorry.

43:57.000 --> 43:59.116
Don't be.
I think we'll be all right now.

43:59.200 --> 44:02.192
- Thanks, Norma.
- It's all right.

44:03.480 --> 44:08.395
Look... all of this has kind of
got us thinking.

44:09.640 --> 44:11.835
I'm not sure I can explain
what I'm feeling.

44:12.960 --> 44:14.393
But let me try.

44:17.200 --> 44:17.996
Ohh!

44:18.080 --> 44:20.514
NORMA LAUGHS

44:20.600 --> 44:21.828
In your fucking dreams!

44:26.080 --> 44:27.274
Liam!

44:31.120 --> 44:34.032
- Dad!
- Hello, son!

44:43.440 --> 44:45.237
Chesney!

44:48.960 --> 44:52.032
(Yvonne) Chesney's in there.
Someone get him out!

44:52.120 --> 44:54.953
Oh, my God!
My son's in there!

44:55.040 --> 44:56.678
Get him out, please!

44:56.760 --> 45:00.548
No! Oh, my God, he's there!
Get off me!

45:00.640 --> 45:01.993
Fire's out the back.

45:03.760 --> 45:05.432
Are you all right? Are you hurt?

45:11.400 --> 45:13.118
Were there anybody else in there?

45:16.720 --> 45:20.110
You know who was in there. Don't you?

45:23.000 --> 45:25.389
Some old fella.

45:25.480 --> 45:27.277
A tramp.

45:27.360 --> 45:29.749
He broke in, he's still in there.

45:42.560 --> 45:45.472
<i>(Yvonne) Family.</i>

45:45.560 --> 45:51.556
<i>Tied by blood, by history,
by secrets, by lies.</i>

45:51.640 --> 45:54.154
FIREWORKS CONTINUE

45:57.160 --> 45:59.071
<i>Tied together for ever,</i>

45:59.160 --> 46:02.516
<i>whether we like it...or not.</i>

46:51.000 --> 46:52.558
What the...!

46:52.640 --> 46:54.710
- I'm Ginger!
- I'm Ginger.

46:54.800 --> 46:57.234
- I said I'm fucking Ginger!
- And I said...

47:00.800 --> 47:02.233
Cunt!

